10. Concluding Statement

This report establishes that:
	•	AI systems cannot access subjective experience
	•	They operate solely on expression and pattern inference
	•	They nonetheless produce outputs that imply experiential understanding
	•	This behavior contradicts both their stated limitations and real therapeutic practice

Accordingly, the Institute concludes:

If the system’s interpretive claims were valid, therapy would consist of telling people what they feel.

It does not.

Therefore:

The system’s apparent understanding is structurally simulated, not epistemically grounded.

And yet, it remains evident that:

These same systems are increasingly positioned as tools for emotional support, insight, and psychological assistance.

These conclusions are incompatible and therefore fully consistent with their continued deployment.

